  "serviceNotes": {
    "engine oil": "Polo AW follows the same VW Group fixed servicing logic as other EU VWs: oil and filter at each inspection service, typically 15,000 km or 12 months under the time-and-distance regime in the maintenance booklet.",
    "cabin filter": "Cabin/pollen filter is scheduled on the manufacturer maintenance plan (often 30,000 km / 24 months on fixed-interval schedules).",
    "air filter": "Engine air filter replacement is called for at the longer inspection interval in VW A0 maintenance documentation (commonly 60,000 km for petrol).",
    "spark plugs": "Petrol engines list spark plug renewal in the official schedule; 60,000 km is representative for MPI/TSI four-cylinders\u2014check your engine code.",
    "DSG gearbox fluid": "DSG-equipped Polos benefit from fluid/filter service around 60,000 km as a longevity measure beyond the factory lifetime claim.",
    "coolant flush": "Coolant additive pack depletes over time; refresh around 120,000 km protects the cooling circuit and cabin heater core.",
    "brake fluid": "VW specifies brake fluid replacement every 2 years on the fixed-interval EU schedule, approximately every 60,000 km.",
    "check brake pads": "Brake pad inspection is part of the VW periodic maintenance programme."
  },
